translated: Lagergren, Elsa Matilda, RN, doctor, Gothenburg, b. 1/3/90 in Evanston, Ill., USA, to Axel Hjalmar L. and Tekla Pettersson. Adopted children: Bertil (Pelle), b. 31, Anita (Tippan), 36. - Education: graduated in Gothenburg '09, medical candidate in Uppsala '14, medical licentiate in Stockholm '21. Work experience: nurse at several hospitals '16-22, assistant doctor at Gothenburg epidemic hospital '22-23, nurse at Gothenburg children's hospital medical department '23-27, intern there '24-27, assistant doctor there '27, doctor at Chicago Municipal Tuberculosis Sanitarium children's department '28, practicing doctor in Gothenburg since '29, doctor at Gothenburg children's center since '30 and at Gothenburg preschool since '31, school doctor at Ma-jorna municipality girls' school since '36 and at municipality middle school since '37.
